{
  "slug": "impeccable",
  "name": "Impeccable",
  "type": "plugin",
  "description": "Design vocabulary and skills for frontend development. Includes 18 skills (17 user-invokable: /polish, /distill, /audit, /bolder, /quieter, etc.) and an enhanced frontend-design skill with curated anti-patterns.",
  "longDescription": "Ships **1 skill** and **17 commands** for frontend design quality.\n\nThe `frontend-design` skill expands Anthropic's original with **7 reference files** covering typography, color and contrast, spatial design, motion, interaction, responsive design, and UX writing. Each reference includes curated anti-patterns — overused fonts, gray-on-color text, nested cards, bounce easing — that explicitly steer the AI away from generic output.\n\n**17 slash commands**: `/audit`, `/critique`, `/normalize`, `/polish`, `/distill`, `/clarify`, `/optimize`, `/harden`, `/animate`, `/colorize`, `/bolder`, `/quieter`, `/delight`, `/extract`, `/adapt`, `/onboard`, `/teach-impeccable`",
  "compatibility": [
    "claude"
  ],
  "sourceType": "community",
  "pluginType": "wrapper",
  "author": {
    "name": "Paul Bakaus"
  },
  "externalUrl": "https://github.com/pbakaus/impeccable/tree/main",
